  "text": "In Envoy v1.31.2, v2 xDS API support has been fully removed. The relevant C++ source files implement: (1) **type_to_endpoint.cc** - maps resource type URLs to v3 service discovery methods (SotW/Delta/REST), with historical comments referencing the v2 service names like 'envoy.api.v2.RouteDiscoveryService'; (2) **utility.h/cc** - contains `checkTransportVersion` which explicitly rejects V2 transport API version with a deprecation error; (3) **subscription_factory_impl.cc** - the subscription factory that calls `checkTransportVersion` and dispatches to GRPC/REST/filesystem factories; (4) **grpc_subscription_factory.cc** - creates SotW and Delta gRPC mux implementations, plus ADS subscription factory; (5) **grpc_mux_impl.cc** and **new_grpc_mux_impl.cc** - the SotW and Delta ADS gRPC mux implementations handling DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse and DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse v3 protos; (6) **xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc** - the unified mux (templated for both SotW and Delta); (7) **watch_map.cc** - manages per-resource-type watch subscriptions; (8) **cluster_manager_impl.cc** - creates and manages the ADS mux (ads_mux_), calling `checkTransportVersion` for ADS config; (9) Various subscription state files handle SotW and Delta protocol state machines.",
